Package edu.uiowa.cs.warp

Class WorkLoad

java.lang.Object
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.VisualizationObject
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.WorkLoadDescription
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.WorkLoad
All Implemented Interfaces:
ReliabilityParameters
public class WorkLoad extends WorkLoadDescription implements ReliabilityParameters
Builds the nodes and flows for the workload described in the workload description file, whose name is passed into the Constructor via the parameter inputFileName. The default values for the constructors are m = 0.9, e2e = 0.99, and numFaults = 1 when the second constructor is used.
Version:
1.4
Author:
sgoddard

    • WorkLoad

      WorkLoad(Double m, Double e2e, String inputFileName)
      Workload constructor creates the Workload object with the specified parameters and the file to be analyzed.
      Parameters:
      m - The minimum acceptable packet reception rate.
      e2e - The end to end reliability expected for the flows of the current file.
      inputFileName - The name of the input file.

    • WorkLoad

      WorkLoad(Integer numFaults, Double m, Double e2e, String inputFileName)
      Second workload constructor that takes the number of acceptable faults as a file input in addition to the parameters already present in the first Workload constructor.
      Parameters:
      numFaults - The number of acceptable faults per edge of the flow for this file.
      m - The minimum acceptable packet reception rate.
      e2e - The end to end reliability expected for the flows of the current file.
      inputFileName - The name of the input file.

    • addFlow

      public void addFlow(String flowName)
      Creates a new flow to be added to to the collection of all flows. This method checks to see if a flow with this name already exists, and if so it replaces it. The index of the number of flows is updated with each addition then the flow is added to a set of the flows in the original order.
      Parameters:
      flowName - The name of the flow.

    • addNodeToFlow

      public void addNodeToFlow(String flowName, String nodeName)
      Creates a node to add to the current flow. First checks if the node already exists, if it does then the node will just be added. If doesn't exist then node is created with the default priority and then added to the map of nodes. Then the priority for this new node is assigned (based on the node's position in the flow).
      Parameters:
      flowName - The name of the flow.
      nodeName - The name of the current node.

    • setFlowsInPriorityOrder

      public void setFlowsInPriorityOrder()
      Method creates an unsorted list of flow objects and through a few Sorting operations, (first by index and second by priority), sets the instanceVariable FlowNamesinPriorityOrder to the a list of names of the nodes of the sorted list in the correct order. In this method, flow index is the secondary key and priority is the primary key. Sorting operations get applied in that order. The lists are sorted using the collected Comparator.comparing(condition) method

    • setFlowsInDMorder

      public void setFlowsInDMorder()
      Method creates an unsorted list of flow objects and through a few Sorting operations, (first by priority and second by deadline), sets the instanceVariable FlowNamesinPriorityOrder to a list of names of the nodes of the sorted list in the correct order. In this method, flow priority is the secondary key and flow deadline is the primary key. Sorting operations get applied in that order. The lists are sorted using the collected Comparator.comparing(condition) method

    • setFlowsInRMorder

      public void setFlowsInRMorder()
      Method creates an unsorted list of flow objects and through a few Sorting operations, (first by priority and second by period), sets the instanceVariable FlowNamesinPriorityOrder to a list of names of the nodes of the sorted list in the correct order. In this method, flow priority is the secondary key and flow period is the primary key. Sorting operations get applied in that order. The lists are sorted using the collected Comparator.comparing(condition) method

    • finalizeCurrentFlow

      public void finalizeCurrentFlow(String flowName)
      If the numberOfFaults in the workLoad Object is greater than 0, this method calls the finalizeFlowWithFixedFaultToleranceMethod. If the number of faults is equal to 0 or represented as a negative number, this method calls the finalizeFlowWithE2eParameters method.
      Parameters:
      flowName - gets passed into both methods that this method calls. (finalizeFlowWithFixedFaultTolerance and finalizeFlowWithE2eParameters

    • nextReleaseTime

      public Integer nextReleaseTime(String flowName, Integer currentTime)
      Method uses flowName to retrieve the flow object with that name. It sets the LastUpdateTime and nextReleaseTime to the current time and returns the flow objects release time.
      Parameters:
      flowName - (String) used to get flow object that has operations done on it.
      currentTime - (Integer) used to set the last updateTima and setNextReleaseTime of the flow object.
      Returns:
      flow.getReleaseTime() (Integer) which is the next release time of the flow object at or after currentTime

    • nextAbsoluteDeadline

      public Integer nextAbsoluteDeadline(String flowName, Integer currentTime)
      Method uses flowName to retrieve the flow object with that name. It sets the LastUpdateTime and nextReleaseTime to the current time and returns the flow objects release time added to the flow deadline.
      Parameters:
      flowName - (String) used to get flow object that has operations done on it.
      currentTime - (Integer) used to set the last updateTima and setNextReleaseTime of the flow object.
      Returns:
      flow.getReleaseTime() + flow.getDeadline() (Integer) which is the next deadline after currentTime

      public String[] getNodeNamesOrderedAlphabetically()
      Makes a list of the set of keys of the nodes instanceVariable. The list of is nodes is sorted, however if names of the nodes are integers then the sort is undesirable. If they are integer strings then they are parsed into Integers and sorted again.
      Returns:
      nodeNames (String[]) list of names of nodes ordered alphabetically.
